# 🍽 Your Restaurant Website — Setup Guide

Welcome! This guide will help you update your website with your own business information.
**You don't need to know how to code.** Follow the steps below.

---

## 📁 Understanding Your Files

```
your-restaurant/
│
├── config.js           ⭐ THIS IS WHERE YOU MAKE ALL YOUR CHANGES
│
├── index.html              (your website — don't edit this)
│
├── assets/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css       (design & colors — don't edit this)
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── main.js         (website logic — don't edit this)
│   └── images/             ⭐ PUT YOUR BUSINESS PHOTOS HERE
│
└── README.md               (this guide)
```

---

## ✏️ Step 1 — Update Your Business Information

Open the file called **`config.js`** in any text editor (Notepad, VS Code, etc.)

Change the values inside the quote marks `"..."` to your own information:

```
business name, phone number, WhatsApp number, email,
address, opening hours, social media links
```

**Save the file when you're done.** Your website will update automatically.

---

## 🖼 Step 2 — Add Your Own Photos

1. Copy your restaurant photos into the **`assets/images/`** folder
2. Name them clearly — example: `hero-bg.jpg`, `dish-jollof.jpg`, `interior.jpg`
3. Open `index.html` in a text editor
4. Find the image you want to replace — look for lines like:
   ```
   src="https://images.unsplash.com/..."
   ```
5. Replace the URL with your image path:
   ```
   src="assets/images/your-photo.jpg"
   ```

**Photo tips:**

- Use JPG format for photos (smaller file size)
- Hero background: at least 1600×900px
- Menu dish photos: at least 800×600px
- Keep each photo under 500KB for fast loading (use tinypng.com to compress)

---

## 🗺 Step 3 — Update Your Google Maps Location

1. Go to **maps.google.com**
2. Search for your restaurant address
3. Click **Share** → **Embed a map** → **Copy HTML**
4. From the copied code, find the part that says `src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?..."`
5. Copy only that link (without the quotes)
6. Paste it into `config.js` where it says `mapEmbedUrl:`

---

## 🎨 Step 4 — Change Your Brand Colors (Optional)

In `config.js`, find the `colors` section and update the hex codes:

```
primary:  "#8B1A00"   ← Your main brand color
accent:   "#F97300"   ← Your highlight color
```

To find your brand colors as hex codes, visit **coolors.co** or use your designer's brand guide.

---

## 📞 Step 5 — Update Your Menu Items

Open `index.html` and search for `menu-card`. Each menu item looks like this:

```html
<h3 class="menu-card__title">Dish Name Here</h3>
<p class="menu-card__desc">Description here</p>
<span class="menu-card__price">₦0,000</span>
```

Change the dish name, description, and price to match your actual menu.

---

## 🚀 Going Live

Once you're happy with everything, send all your files to your developer
and they will upload your website to the internet with a custom domain name.

